<br>
Mastery of Pain I - Doesnt give enough return to make it worth it as an entry level skill.  This isn't going to be a make or break skill for PvE for sure, and at level 1 will provide such infrequent crits that your likely to wish you had spent the points on something else for PvP.<br>
<br>
MOC - Very useful in PvE and PvP.  Especially given the high amount of mana burned by our shouts/snares/mez.  For only 3 points and no pre-req I don't think I could recommend a more useful RA.<br>
<br>
First Aid - So so at level 1, very good at level 2.  Easily 30% per level as advertised if not a little bit more for Skalds.  One thing to remember is that this is a pre-req for Ignore Pain which will require FA2.<br>
<br>
Serenity - skip it skip it skip it.  What a waste.  Do yourself a favor and just buy MOC.<br>
<br>
Tireless - some folks say they like tireless.  I personally see next to no difference with it.  Skalds chew through endurance so fast that it would take a major boost to end regen to make any sort of difference.  <br>
<br>
Beyond those reasonable entry level RA's your looking at the stat increases, which personally as difficult as it is to attain RA's at the higher ranks - you should definately carefully consider your long term goals before buying anything.  Here is what I would suggest -<br>
<br>
MOC<br>
FA I<br>
FA II<br>
IP<br>
Purge<br>
<br>
After that your looking at fluf anyway - I'm personally considering FA III for another 30% heal.  As skalds FA is nearly as useful as IP since we can mez our opponents, quit combat, wait the 3 seconds and use FA then jump back into combat.  Don't underestimate the importance of a good in combat full heal mind you, but I use FA ALL the time and it works fantastically.  15 Min timer makes it even better.<br>
